The paper deals with steganography, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves generating image-like containers using Deep Convolutional Generative Adversarial Networks (DCGAN), which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of standard steganography algorithms, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). The use of machine learning techniques such as DCGAN suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
